<i>The rain we've seen between 
the Kinki and Kanto regions</i>

00:02:13.830 --> 00:02:15.770
<i>will start to let up tomorrow morning,</i>

00:02:15.770 --> 00:02:17.920
<i>bringing sunny weather 
to most of the country.</i>

00:02:18.280 --> 00:02:21.100
<i>However, an area of low 
pressure in northern Hokkaido</i>

00:02:20.940 --> 00:02:22.380
Okay! I've made up my mind!

00:02:21.100 --> 00:02:24.900
<i>may bring periods of less 
favorable weather for a time.</i>

00:02:22.380 --> 00:02:25.490
Next weekend, I'm inviting my friend over!

00:02:25.490 --> 00:02:28.040
<i>Now, let's take a look at temperatures.</i>

00:02:26.210 --> 00:02:28.050
How many? How many?

00:02:28.050 --> 00:02:31.050
One! I don't have the guts 
for any more than that yet!

00:02:28.500 --> 00:02:31.050
<i>Temperatures in western Japan will be two 
to three degrees higher than today.</i>

00:02:31.040 --> 00:02:35.710
Erika-chan, right? The one you knew 
was interesting at first glance?

00:02:31.460 --> 00:02:35.820
<i>It might even be warm enough to break a 
little sweat in Kagoshima and Kumamoto.</i>

00:02:35.710 --> 00:02:38.700
Yeah! I gotta go clean my room!

00:02:35.820 --> 00:02:39.700
<i>Eastern Japan should also be quite warm, 
just right for doing the laundry.</i>

00:02:38.700 --> 00:02:40.310
I'll help!

00:02:40.310 --> 00:02:43.130
<i>Finally, the week-long forecast, 
from Nagoya to Naha.</i>

00:02:40.310 --> 00:02:43.130
Wait, dinner's almost ready!

00:02:43.130 --> 00:02:44.390
Later!

00:02:43.130 --> 00:02:46.480
<i>Okinawa will see some very rough 
weather through the weekend.</i>

00:02:44.390 --> 00:02:45.810
Later!

00:02:49.070 --> 00:02:53.020
<i>A week ago, I was full of confidence.</i>

00:02:53.730 --> 00:02:55.230
<b>(Mon.)</b>

00:02:55.240 --> 00:02:58.520
<i>It's my first time inviting 
someone my age over to my house.</i>

